            "default_open_3": "No",
            "title_3": "How long is the battery range on a full charge?",
            "answer_3": "<p>The 48V/23.4AH lithium battery offers a range of 35–53 miles (56–85 km) depending on load, terrain, speed, and temperature</p>",
            "default_open_4": "No",
            "title_4": "What rider height is the IN10 suitable for?",
            "answer_4": "<p>Recommended for users 120–175 cm tall and aged 14 years and above.</p>",
            "default_open_5": "No",
            "title_5": "How long does it take to fully charge the battery?",
            "answer_5": "<p>With the included 48V/5A charger, a full charge typically takes 5–6 hours.</p>",
            "default_open_6": "No",
            "title_6": "What type of motor does it use?",
            "answer_6": "<p>The IN10 features a 1200W rated / 3000W peak direct drive brushless motor, offering strong acceleration and climbing power.</p>",
            "default_open_7": "No",
            "title_7": "Is the Yozma IN10 waterproof?",
            "answer_7": "<p>Yes, it is rated IPX6, which means it can withstand heavy rain and splashes from all directions.</p>",
            "default_open_8": "No",
            "title_8": "Does it come fully assembled?",
            "answer_8": "<p>Yozma IN 10 comes 90% pre-assembled. You’ll need to install parts like the front wheel, handlebars, fenders, and pedals. We provide step-by-step instructions and video guides, and most people finish assembly in 3-5 minutes using basic tools.</p>",
            "default_open_9": "No",
            "title_9": "What is the max load capacity?",
            "answer_9": "<p>The Yozma IN10 supports up to 120 kg (264 lbs).</p>",
            "default_open_10": "No",
            "title_10": "Does the IN 10 have any anti-theft features?",
            "answer_10": "<p>Yes, our e-bikes come with essential anti-theft features. The battery is secured with a lock and can only be removed using the key, effectively preventing unauthorized removal. </p>"
          }
        },
